how to configure CAN 

1. first of all power off the pi
sudo poweroff

2. do the configuration 
sudo nano /boot/firmware/config.txt

3. add the section in the end 
dtparam=spi=on
dtoverlay=i2c0
dtoverlay=spi1-3cs
dtoverlay=mcp2515,spi1-1,oscillator=16000000,interrupt=22
dtoverlay=mcp2515,spi1-2,oscillator=16000000,interrupt=13

>>>>>>>>> in order to save the session follow the respected command 

control + o 
enter 
control + x

4. reboot 
sudo reboot

5. check the HAT device detected
dmesg | grep spi1

6. then write this to detect. 
ip link show

>>>>> it will look lik can0 and can1

7. bring CAN UP
sudo ip link set can0 up type can bitrate 1000000
sudo ip link set can1 up type can bitrate 1000000
sudo ifconfig can0 txqueuelen 65536
sudo ifconfig can1 txqueuelen 65536

8. check the ip links

ip link show can0
ip link show can1

9. quick test on 2 terminal 

>>>> terminal 1 
candump can0

>>>> on terminal 2 
cansend can1 000#11223344
